1
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:27,300
<font color="#4096d1">海貍</font>

2
00:01:32,292 --> 00:01:35,739
這就是沃特·布萊克
This is a picture of Walter Black,

3
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:39,471
一個陷入絕望的抑鬱癥患者
a hopelessly depressed individual.

4
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:44,942
而在他內心某處 住著一個曾經墜入愛河
Somewhere inside him is a man who fell in love,

5
00:01:46,139 --> 00:01:47,209
組建起美滿家庭
who started a family...

6
00:01:47,807 --> 00:01:49,650
接著我醒了
And then I woke up.

7
00:01:50,076 --> 00:01:52,113
...事業有成的人
...who ran a successful company.

8
00:01:54,848 --> 00:01:57,727
但這個人卻已經消失不見了
That man has gone missing.

9
00:01:58,451 --> 00:01:59,521
不管他怎樣努力
No matter what he's tried,

10
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:03,763
用盡一切辦法
and he's tried everything,

11
00:02:05,458 --> 00:02:06,732
沃特對他的離去卻束手無策
Walter can't seem to bring him back.

12
00:02:09,696 --> 00:02:10,970
就好像他實際上已經死了
It's as if he's died

13
00:02:11,030 --> 00:02:13,806
卻沒能帶上他的肉體一起離開
but hasn't had the good sense to take his body with him.

14
00:02:14,934 --> 00:02:18,472
所以大部分的時間他都用來睡覺
So, mostly, what he does is sleep.

15
00:02:26,012 --> 00:02:28,652
他父親曾經引以為傲的玩具公司的股份
Shares in his father's once-proud toy company

16
00:02:28,715 --> 00:02:31,457
如今卻和沃特的感受一樣 變得一文不值
are now almost as worthless as Walter feels.

17
00:02:33,453 --> 00:02:36,525
他那好像節日賀卡一樣美滿幸福的家庭
His family used to resemble something out of a holiday greeting card

18
00:02:36,589 --> 00:02:39,729
現在卻充滿了無休止的哀傷
but now seems to be in perpetual mourning.

19
00:02:40,860 --> 00:02:45,502
他最小的孩子亨利已經成為老師口中的"獨行俠"
Henry, his youngest, has become what his teachers call "solitary. "

20
00:02:46,266 --> 00:02:47,973
總有一天他會成為隱形人
He'd like to become invisible one day

21
00:02:48,034 --> 00:02:50,640
而不僅僅是被他親生父親忽視
instead of merely unnoticed by his own father.

22
00:02:53,139 --> 00:02:54,948
而珀特 他的大兒子
And, Porter, his eldest?

23
00:02:55,408 --> 00:02:58,787
害怕會變得像他父親那樣
Well, he's terrified of becoming just like his father.

24
00:02:59,646 --> 00:03:03,788
他的任務? 就是記錄他倆之間每個可怕的相似點
His mission? To catalog every dreaded similarity that links them.

25
00:03:04,584 --> 00:03:05,585
每一次咬嘴唇
Every lip bite.

26
00:03:05,652 --> 00:03:08,792
每一次把脖子弄得吱嘎響 每一次無意識的行為
Every neck crack. Every involuntary behavior.

27
00:03:09,222 --> 00:03:10,997
他決心一個一個地將它們抹去
He plans to erase them one by one.

28
00:03:13,226 --> 00:03:17,936
妻子梅勒迪斯埋首於她的工程事務
His wife, Meredith, has hidden herself behind her engineering work

29
00:03:17,997 --> 00:03:21,945
晚上與東京的電話會議 以及雲霄飛車的設計工作
and nighttime conference calls to Tokyo and roller coaster designs.

30
00:03:22,368 --> 00:03:24,974
任何能讓她擺脫丈夫不在身邊 這一事實的事
Anything to drown out the reality of an absent husband.

31
00:03:26,806 --> 00:03:29,235
沃特的抑鬱癥就像一滴墨汁 
Walter's depression is an ink 

32
00:03:29,235 --> 00:03:31,415
影響著所有他遇到的事
that stains everything it touches.

33
00:03:32,779 --> 00:03:35,487
像一個黑洞 吞噬他身邊所有的人
A black hole that swallows all who get near.

34
00:03:38,685 --> 00:03:40,926
他們都在等待著他醒過來
They've all been waiting for him to wake up,

35
00:03:42,589 --> 00:03:43,590
重新振作起來
to snap out of it,

36
00:03:45,158 --> 00:03:46,660
但他遲遲不見好轉
but he hasn't.

37
00:03:48,828 --> 00:03:51,502
所以 梅勒迪斯做了最後唯一能做的
So, Meredith does the only thing left to do

38
00:03:52,832 --> 00:03:55,005
說了最後唯一能說的
and says the only thing left to say.

39
00:03:57,203 --> 00:03:58,204
再見
Goodbye.

40
00:04:14,988 --> 00:04:17,628
賈裡德 你這科都要掛了
Jared, you're failing this class.

41
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:20,339
你真覺得你突然交出一份滿分的論文 
Do you honestly think you can suddenly hand in an "A" paper 

42
00:04:20,339 --> 00:04:21,332
你能逃之夭夭?
and get away with it?

43
00:04:21,394 --> 00:04:22,395
那赫克托呢?
What about Hector?

44
00:04:22,829 --> 00:04:24,557
你幫他在家庭發展上拿到了A
You got him an "A" in Family Development.

45
00:04:25,698 --> 00:04:28,542
聽著 我從來沒有幫赫克托寫過東西 明白了嗎?
Look, I've never written anything for Hector. All right?

46
00:04:28,601 --> 00:04:31,309
如果他是那麼和你說的 他就是個騙子
If he told you differently, he's a liar.

47
00:04:32,138 --> 00:04:34,243
想想 即使我真幫他寫了論文
Hypothetically, had I written him something,

48
00:04:34,307 --> 00:04:36,514
就得繼續不斷把他的分數提高
we would have raised his grades incrementally.

49
00:04:36,976 --> 00:04:40,890
如果真是這樣 那麼他最後才會拿到A
And if that happened, then, yes, he might have turned in an "A" paper.

50
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:43,928
在他經常掛掉的課上 拿到B就算不錯了
He might even be making a "B" in a class that he used to be failing.

51
00:04:43,983 --> 00:04:46,409
所以 要是有人想讓我幫忙 
So, if someone wanted me to do this, 

52
00:04:46,409 --> 00:04:47,932
那就得照著他們的樣子辦事
and do it as them,

53
00:04:47,987 --> 00:04:50,271
以他們的口吻 在他們的能力之內
in their voice and at their skill level,

54
00:04:51,024 --> 00:04:53,061
我會告訴他們要不按我說的辦
I would say that they could either do it my way

55
00:04:53,126 --> 00:04:56,539
要不試試你的運氣 從網上買幾篇廢紙
or take your chances buying some piece of shit off the Internet.

56
00:04:56,596 --> 00:04:59,917
每次200?      要是嫌多就自己寫去
$200 every time?        If it's too much, write it yourself.

57
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:03,269
比大麻還貴
More than I pay for weed.

58
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,800
(體育館 明天4點)

59
00:05:43,276 --> 00:05:44,277
對不起 孩子
Sorry, buddy.

60
00:05:45,144 --> 00:05:46,851
你又沒看到我
You passed me again.

61
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:49,421
我知道 寶貝 我那是在找你啊
I know, honey. I was looking.

62
00:05:53,386 --> 00:05:55,366
今天怎麼樣?
How was your day?

63
00:05:56,589 --> 00:05:58,068
和別人說話了嗎?
Did you talk to anyone?

64
00:05:59,092 --> 00:06:00,969
我想是的
I guess.

65
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:02,904
新朋友還是老朋友?
A new person or an old person?

66
00:06:03,563 --> 00:06:04,564
新的
New.

67
00:06:04,630 --> 00:06:06,803
很好 你們都說了什麼呢?
Good. What did you talk about?

68
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,301
他說我是慫蛋
He said I was a ball-licker.

69
00:06:10,136 --> 00:06:13,998
我說我不是 他就把我扔進垃圾箱裡了
I told him I wasn't, and he threw me in the dumpster.

70
00:06:15,074 --> 00:06:16,075
什麼
What?

71
00:06:17,643 --> 00:06:19,486
你告訴老師了嗎?
Did you tell your teacher?

72
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:21,828
是她把我從垃圾箱裡弄出來的
She got me out of the dumpster.

73
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:29,495
這肯定有些誤會
Well, this must be some kind of misunderstanding,

74
00:06:29,495 --> 00:06:32,927
我們必須要調解糾正他們的...
and we just have to realign or correct their...

75
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:34,936
我會和老師談談
I'll talk to the teacher.

76
00:06:36,996 --> 00:06:38,031
爸爸走了?
Is Dad gone?

77
00:06:40,032 --> 00:06:42,376
不 他沒離開 寶貝
No. He's not gone, honey.

78
00:06:43,569 --> 00:06:46,127
只是我們都覺得不在一起生活比較好
We just agreed that it's better if we don't live together anymore. 

79
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:47,985
知道嗎?
Okay?

80
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:22,738
你想在海的另一邊尋找什麼 孩子
What do you look for beyond the sea, Grasshopper?

81
00:08:24,103 --> 00:08:25,912
知之甚少的那部分自我
That part of me which I know little of.

82
00:08:26,873 --> 00:08:29,353
我的前世
The past of which I was born.

83
00:08:29,408 --> 00:08:31,752
那麼有一天 你會找到它的
Then, some day, you must seek it.

84
00:08:32,111 --> 00:08:35,058
尋求過去是對的嗎? 波大師
Is it good to seek the past, Master Po?

85
00:08:36,949 --> 00:08:38,895
它不會擾亂現在嗎?
Does it not rob the present?

86
00:08:38,951 --> 00:08:42,296
如果一個人總是沉溺在過去 他就會毀掉現在
If a man dwells on the past, then he robs the present.

87
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:46,769
但是如果忽視過去 那麼他則會毀掉未來
But if a man ignores the past, he may rob the future.

88
00:08:47,093 --> 00:08:49,953
命運的種子需要細心呵護 
The seeds of our destiny are nurtured...

89
00:08:49,953 --> 00:08:51,372
這就是它們的美好之處 孩子
That's beautiful, Grasshopper.

90
00:08:53,499 --> 00:08:55,775
來 喝酒
Here. Here you go.

91
00:08:57,069 --> 00:08:58,412
你不喝
You moved.

92
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:22,422
嘿!
Oi!

93
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:46,419
你知道 既然我們現在正做些改變
You know, since we're making changes around here,

94
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:49,517
也許你需要請個水管工之類的
maybe you want to get, like, a plumber or something.

95
00:10:49,749 --> 00:10:51,729
我是說這地方都快塌了
I mean, this place is falling apart.

96
00:10:52,518 --> 00:10:53,492
那實在太糟了 
Well, that's too bad, 

97
00:10:53,492 --> 00:10:56,626
我們對此實在沒什麼辦法 不是嗎?
because there's really not much we can do about it, is there?

98
00:10:58,024 --> 00:11:01,169
哇哦 放鬆點 我站在你這邊 
Whoa, relax. I'm on your side, okay. 

99
00:11:01,169 --> 00:11:02,405
我很高興你把他踢出去了
I'm glad you kicked him out.

100
00:11:02,895 --> 00:11:07,241
這只是餐桌上的討論而已
I'm just saying this whole eating-at-the-table thing together.

101
00:11:07,299 --> 00:11:10,337
我的意思是 你打算讓他在外面多久?
I mean, that's... How long do you expect us to keep that up?

102
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:13,309
不知道 珀特
I don't know, Porter.

103
00:11:13,372 --> 00:11:15,374
也許等到我們重新學會相互尊重?
Maybe until we start respecting each other again?

104
00:11:15,441 --> 00:11:20,515
也許等到我們開始關心對方今天過得怎麼樣
You know, maybe when we start asking each other how was our day

105
00:11:20,579 --> 00:11:22,024
把盤子清理乾淨的時候
and clearing out the dishes...

106
00:11:22,081 --> 00:11:24,254
也許我也該制定一張路線圖
Maybe I should get a paper route, too.

107
00:11:27,019 --> 00:11:28,862
接著 我要猜這個數字
Then I'm going to guess the number.

108
00:11:31,257 --> 00:11:34,067
如果我才對了 我們就開始小貓咪的故事
If I guess right, we do the kitten story.

109
00:11:35,661 --> 00:11:37,538
今晚有兩個故事 實在太頭疼了
Two big stories to get to tonight, unfortunately...

110
00:11:44,437 --> 00:11:45,677
醒醒
Wake up.

111
00:11:48,174 --> 00:11:50,711
起來 你個沒用的笨蛋
Wake up, you worthless sod.

112
00:11:54,513 --> 00:11:56,754
天吶 瞧瞧你的樣子
Bloody hell. Look at you.

113
00:11:58,651 --> 00:12:01,689
醉得不省人事 被電視機壓在下面
Stone-drunk and flattened by a television.

114
00:12:06,025 --> 00:12:09,996
你真是在給自己寫訃告啊 沃特
That's quite an obituary you're working up for yourself, Walter.

115
00:12:25,845 --> 00:12:26,983
走開
Leave me alone.

116
00:12:29,014 --> 00:12:32,860
不不不不 我才不要走 你不想我走開的
No. Can't do that. You don't want that.

117
00:12:33,385 --> 00:12:38,733
因為我是唯一一個真正瞭解你內心感受的人
'Cause I'm the only one what knows how you really feel.

118
00:12:42,094 --> 00:12:44,472
人人都需要個朋友 沃特
Everybody needs a friend, Walter.

119
00:12:45,798 --> 00:12:47,505
我就是你的朋友
And you've got me.

120
00:12:49,201 --> 00:12:52,546
就是因為這你把那些自我救贖的書讀了個遍
That's why you read all them useless self-help books.

121
00:12:53,873 --> 00:12:59,221
什麼《心情雞湯》《正向思考》《友情秘訣》
Chicken Soup, Positive Thinking, How to Win Friends.

122
00:12:59,545 --> 00:13:03,091
哪本書教你把電視往自己腦袋上砸的?
Which one has the chapter about dropping the telly on your head?

123
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:05,724
我病了
I'm sick.

124
00:13:06,719 --> 00:13:09,825
的確 沃特 這點我們達成共識
Yeah, Walt. On that, we agree.

125
00:13:12,525 --> 00:13:15,904
問題是 你想不想好起來?
The question is, do you want to get better?

126
00:13:21,667 --> 00:13:23,772
我做不到
I can't.

127
00:13:23,836 --> 00:13:26,817
是啊是啊是啊 你得了抑鬱癥 哦 是啊
Yeah, yeah, yeah. You're depressed. Yeah.

128
00:13:26,872 --> 00:13:29,876
昏昏沉沉 鬱鬱寡歡
Lethargic. Anhedonia.

129
00:13:30,342 --> 00:13:31,582
醒醒吧!
Wake up!

130
00:13:33,112 --> 00:13:36,059
那些書還有小藥片 那都是些棉花糖
Books and pills. They're cotton candy.

131
00:13:36,849 --> 00:13:39,329
你看太多家居裝飾的節目
You've seen too many home-improvement shows.

132
00:13:39,385 --> 00:13:40,386
以至於你真覺得僅僅靠
You think you can just

133
00:13:40,452 --> 00:13:43,865
重新刷個漆 重新挪一下家俱的位置
splash up some paint and rearrange the furniture,

134
00:13:43,923 --> 00:13:45,489
接著所有的一切都會恢復正常
and everything will be all right.

135
00:13:46,192 --> 00:13:51,232
你想不想做些改變? 我是說 真正的改變?
You want things to change? I mean, really change?

136
00:13:52,731 --> 00:13:55,007
你要忘了那些家居裝潢的想法 沃特
You gotta forget about home improvement, Walter.

137
00:13:55,367 --> 00:13:59,179
你該去把這該死的房子炸掉
You have gotta blow up the whole bloody building.

138
00:14:09,148 --> 00:14:10,491
那麼你要怎麼做呢? 沃特
What are you gonna do, Walter?

139
00:14:12,284 --> 00:14:13,888
炸了它      大聲點!
Blow it up.        Louder!

140
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,365
炸了它      大聲點!
Blow it up.        Louder!

141
00:14:16,589 --> 00:14:21,504
炸了它! 把他媽的炸了! 炸了它! 炸了它!
Blow it up! Blow it the fuck up! Blow it up! Blow it up!

142
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:22,561
很好
Right.

143
00:14:22,995 --> 00:14:24,497
太對了 夥計
Too right, mate.

144
00:14:24,763 --> 00:14:27,107
你可以把它都炸了 再重新開始
You can blow it up. Start again.

145
00:14:29,902 --> 00:14:31,313
你是誰?
Who are you?

146
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:38,970
我是海貍先生 我為拯救你那苦逼的生活而來
I'm the Beaver, Walter, and I'm here to save your goddamn life.

147
00:14:44,183 --> 00:14:45,321
嗨
Hey.

148
00:14:46,018 --> 00:14:48,555
抱歉 我一定又錯過他了 他擠進人群裡了
I'm sorry. I must have passed him again. He just blends in.

149
00:14:48,621 --> 00:14:50,651
不 他父親早就把他接走了
No, his dad picked him up early.

150
00:14:51,156 --> 00:14:52,157
沃特?
Walter?

151
00:14:52,324 --> 00:14:57,103
他說他給你發了短信 你丈夫真是個與眾不同的人
He said he sent you a text. Your husband is quite a character.

152
00:15:16,348 --> 00:15:18,021
媽媽 你真該來看看我們的傑作
Mom, you gotta see what we did.

153
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:21,087
好啊 你爸爸呢?      快來 我給你看
Okay. Where's your father?        Come on! I'll show you.

154
00:15:24,623 --> 00:15:26,034
你把回憶存在裡面
You put your memory in it.

155
00:15:26,659 --> 00:15:28,195
你從哪找到的?
Where'd you get that?

156
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:30,399
這是我們做的      你和你爸爸?
We made it.        You and your dad?

157
00:15:30,963 --> 00:15:32,203
我和海貍先生
Me and the Beaver.

158
00:15:33,232 --> 00:15:34,609
海貍先生?
The Beaver?

159
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:42,176
知道沃特把磨石機塞哪了嗎?
Any idea where Walter stuffed the power sander

160
00:15:42,241 --> 00:15:44,016
兩年前你送他的那個聖誕禮物
you gave him two Christmases ago?

161
00:15:45,844 --> 00:15:46,845
不知道?
No?

162
00:15:47,346 --> 00:15:49,383
沒關係 我們能應付
No trouble. We'll make do.

163
00:15:49,481 --> 00:15:52,485
