00:25:57,722 --> 00:26:01,027
不是因為什麼特殊的才能或是優點 
Not through any particular skill or merit, 

328
00:26:01,028 --> 00:26:03,196
只是沃特是繼承人
but because Walter was next in line

329
00:26:03,328 --> 00:26:07,868
而不是站在那的資深副總
rather than our infinitely more qualified VP standing right here.

330
00:26:08,466 --> 00:26:09,467
你好 親愛的
Hello, love.

331
00:26:09,534 --> 00:26:14,130
沃特 嗯 還沒做好接手這工作的準備
It was a job Walter was, well, ill-prepared to handle.

332
00:26:14,839 --> 00:26:16,250
基本上...
Basically, well...

333
00:26:17,676 --> 00:26:19,212
沃特是個失敗者
Walter's been a loser.

334
00:26:20,278 --> 00:26:27,069
這就是現在他退出 而讓我接手職位的原因
Which is why, as of now, he is resigning and putting me in charge.

335
00:26:27,352 --> 00:26:29,573
那麼 在你們決定要把我扔到鐵軌上 
So, before you decide to run me out on a rail 

336
00:26:29,573 --> 00:26:31,392
把我燒死之前
with all the flaming torches and pitchforks,

337
00:26:31,456 --> 00:26:33,075
給我五分鐘 聽我把話講完 
hear me out, give me five minutes, 

338
00:26:33,075 --> 00:26:37,601
之後要殺要剮悉聽尊便
then you may tear me to shreds, if you like.

339
00:26:37,696 --> 00:26:42,441
首先 我將會取消對單個項目的管理
First, I will be ceding control of all individual projects

340
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:44,002
回到以前的團隊管理
back to the teams themselves.

341
00:26:44,069 --> 00:26:45,412
也就是說你們自由了
That means you will be free

342
00:26:45,503 --> 00:26:49,041
你們會回到一開始的本職工作
and entrusted to do the jobs you was hired to do in the first place.

343
00:26:49,107 --> 00:26:50,108
你好 漢克
Hello, Hank.

344
00:26:50,175 --> 00:26:54,000
其次 我們會重新整頓 恢復生氣 重新參展
Second, we will revamp, revitalize, re-launch

345
00:26:54,012 --> 00:26:57,550
六周後的
at the International Game and Toy Manufacturers Expo

346
00:26:57,616 --> 00:27:00,392
國際遊戲暨玩具廠商展覽會
in six weeks' time.

347
00:27:00,819 --> 00:27:03,826
我明白你們對我的領導能力
Now, I know there's a very high degree of skepticism 

348
00:27:03,826 --> 00:27:05,992
有諸多質疑
about my ability to lead.

349
00:27:06,157 --> 00:27:07,431
不是嗎?
Isn't that right?

350
00:27:07,492 --> 00:27:10,871
一個中年老男人 他的手臂塞在我屁股裡
I mean, middle-aged man with his arm stuck up my bum. Right?

351
00:27:11,096 --> 00:27:15,272
誰不會懷疑我呢? 不過我也會給你們以下選擇
Who wouldn't doubt me? But I'll make you the following deal.

352
00:27:15,333 --> 00:27:19,975
給我兩周的時間 就兩周 兩周之後
You give me two weeks, just two, and at the end of that time,

353
00:27:20,038 --> 00:27:23,281
任何人想要離開都會得到一筆豐厚的解雇賠償金
anyone who wants to resign will receive severance pay

354
00:27:23,341 --> 00:27:25,582
還有一封漂亮的推薦信
and a glowing letter of recommendation.

355
00:27:25,644 --> 00:27:28,818
一言為定 絕無例外      抱歉?
No questions asked, no exceptions.        Excuse me?

356
00:27:28,947 --> 00:27:30,392
你到底是誰?
And who exactly are you supposed to be?

357
00:27:31,149 --> 00:27:34,062
天吶 我忘記自我介紹了?
Bollocks. Did I forget to introduce myself?

358
00:27:34,653 --> 00:27:37,532
你們可以叫我海貍先生
You may simply call me the Beaver.

359
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:46,400
太牛了
Impressive.

360
00:27:48,633 --> 00:27:49,634
那麼 你需要瞭解什麼?
So, what do you need to know?

361
00:27:51,369 --> 00:27:55,044
我想首先我得知道你要說些什麼?
Well, I guess the first thing is, what do you want to say?

362
00:27:58,009 --> 00:27:59,886
這就是問題所在
Well, that's kind of the problem.

363
00:28:00,211 --> 00:28:03,420
我是說 我的成績不錯 算是個人物 還有什麼?
I mean, I got good grades. Big deal. What do I know?

364
00:28:03,481 --> 00:28:07,258
那你做這些事的時候你想別人怎麼看你?
Okay. Well, how do you want people to feel when you're done?

365
00:28:07,519 --> 00:28:13,128
我覺得我只想著不要讓他們
I guess I just want them to feel not

366
00:28:14,125 --> 00:28:15,399
失望
let down.

367
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:16,528
"不要失望"
"Not let down. "

368
00:28:17,028 --> 00:28:18,336
這點很好
That's powerful.

369
00:28:19,931 --> 00:28:22,104
"我很激動很興奮 你怎麼樣?"
"I'm excited, pumped. How are you doing?"

370
00:28:22,167 --> 00:28:24,204
"我? 我從不讓人失望"
"Me? I'm not let down. "

371
00:28:25,470 --> 00:28:28,280
我告訴過你我很挫的 所以我才需要你
I told you that I suck. This is why I need you.

372
00:28:28,339 --> 00:28:31,877
好吧 你是啦啦隊長 出了名的急性子
Okay, well, you're a cheerleader, notorious hothead.

373
00:28:31,943 --> 00:28:33,980
能說說你八年級是怎麼被開除的麼?
Could we talk about you getting expelled from the eighth grade?

374
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,717
你怎麼知道這事?
How did you find out about that?

375
00:28:38,083 --> 00:28:40,188
有網絡無秘密
No secrets on the Internet.

376
00:28:40,719 --> 00:28:41,720
你幹了什麼?
What did you do?

377
00:28:41,786 --> 00:28:43,026
你偷了誰的百科全書?
Did you steal some encyclopedias?

378
00:28:43,088 --> 00:28:45,125
吸煙?      不是
Chew some nicotine gum        No.

379
00:28:45,190 --> 00:28:47,101
那是什麼? 嘲笑小胖墩?
What? Tease a fat kid?

380
00:28:47,625 --> 00:28:48,626
住口
Shut up.

381
00:28:49,127 --> 00:28:50,197
好吧 那麼究竟是什麼?
All right. So, what is it?

382
00:28:52,831 --> 00:28:54,139
我正在標記
I was tagging.

383
00:28:56,835 --> 00:28:58,075
標記?
Tagging?

384
00:28:59,704 --> 00:29:00,910
就像...
Like...

385
00:29:04,609 --> 00:29:05,610
像隨手塗鴉?
Like graffiti tagging?

386
00:29:06,144 --> 00:29:10,183
更像是藝術創作 只是這是非法的
More like art. It was just illegal.

387
00:29:12,117 --> 00:29:15,587
那現在那個叛逆的作品在哪?
Where's all this rebel-artist shit now?

388
00:29:16,121 --> 00:29:18,123
很久之前的事了
That was a long time ago.

389
00:29:18,990 --> 00:29:22,460
你還保留了一些 不是嗎?
You still have some, don't you? Yeah.

390
00:29:22,660 --> 00:29:24,765
給我看看      不
Show me, please.        No.

391
00:29:25,730 --> 00:29:26,620
如果你給我看 
If you show me, 

392
00:29:26,620 --> 00:29:28,871
我就能寫出能讓你解放西藏的演講
I will write you a speech that you could free Tibet with.

393
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,798
為什麼你這麼想看?
Why do you want to see it so bad?

394
00:29:31,569 --> 00:29:33,276
因為我想要驚喜
Because I like to be surprised.

395
00:29:38,076 --> 00:29:40,420
我們得快點      好吧
We have to be quick.        All right.

396
00:29:42,313 --> 00:29:44,054
這是誰的房間?
Whose room is this?

397
00:29:44,349 --> 00:29:45,657
沒人住
No one's.

398
00:29:54,993 --> 00:29:56,199
噢 天啊
Oh, wow.

399
00:30:06,771 --> 00:30:08,070
我想畫張全景的 
I like to do it big. 

400
00:30:09,100 --> 00:30:11,915
有高速公路 各種建築 廣告牌什麼的
Like freeways, buildings, billboards.

401
00:30:13,211 --> 00:30:18,354
而且速度很快 好像我一小時能跑百萬英里
And fast. Like I'm running a million miles an hour.

402
00:30:20,185 --> 00:30:21,721
不用費力去思考 你懂嗎?
No thinking, you know?

403
00:30:24,189 --> 00:30:25,429
你為什麼放棄了?
Why did you stop?

404
00:30:29,194 --> 00:30:32,664
因為我被逮到了 我媽媽受不了這個
'Cause I got caught and my mom couldn't take it.

405
00:30:33,531 --> 00:30:36,512
不管怎樣 我把它們都扔了
Anyway, I threw them all away.

406
00:30:36,568 --> 00:30:37,569
肯定有人喜歡他們
Someone must have liked them.

407
00:30:39,037 --> 00:30:41,881
把它們從垃圾裡救回來 不是嗎?
Pulled them out of the trash, didn't they?

408
00:30:43,107 --> 00:30:45,246
誰會那麼干呢?      你們在這幹嗎?
Who was it?        What are you doing in here?

409
00:30:47,412 --> 00:30:50,325
我只是帶著珀特在屋裡轉轉
I was just showing Porter around the house.

410
00:30:52,183 --> 00:30:54,424
我們在一個數學小組
He's on the math team with me.

411
00:30:54,886 --> 00:30:56,627
好吧      時間不早了
Right.        Time to go.

412
00:30:59,791 --> 00:31:02,601
對我媽的態度 我很抱歉
Hey, I'm sorry about my mom.

413
00:31:03,728 --> 00:31:05,935
她只是 你知道...      沒事
She's just, you know...        That's fine.

414
00:31:10,535 --> 00:31:12,310
你知道 你非常
You know, you are

415
00:31:14,439 --> 00:31:16,379
非常奇怪
so much weirder...

416
00:31:19,310 --> 00:31:23,001
不是奇怪 我的意思是 與眾不同
Not weird, I just mean, like, different, I guess.

417
00:31:23,448 --> 00:31:26,861
你比我想像中更加獨特
You're a lot more different than I thought you'd be.

418
00:31:27,385 --> 00:31:29,216
對於一個我出高價
You know, for someone I'm paying a lot of money 

419
00:31:29,216 --> 00:31:30,331
請他幫我寫演講稿的人來說
to write a speech for me,

420
00:31:30,331 --> 00:31:31,656
你有點詞不達意
you're not very articulate.

421
00:31:32,757 --> 00:31:34,341
我的文筆比口才好
I'm much better on paper.

422
00:31:35,026 --> 00:31:36,369
我們拭目以待
We'll see.

423
00:31:37,495 --> 00:31:41,375
謝謝你沒笑我
Thank you for not laughing, I guess.

424
00:31:41,833 --> 00:31:42,834
我不會那麼干
I wouldn't do that.

425
00:31:43,101 --> 00:31:44,739
我不會嘲笑你
I wouldn't laugh.

426
00:31:45,637 --> 00:31:46,707
很好
Good.

427
00:31:49,173 --> 00:31:50,777
非常好
Very, very good.

428
00:32:05,790 --> 00:32:10,899
*記憶中我們相見在北海邊*
*We salute at the threshold of the North Sea in my mind*

429
00:32:11,663 --> 00:32:14,940
*點點頭對著帶我來這的一堆煩心事*
*And a nod to the boredom that drove me here*

430
00:32:14,999 --> 00:32:19,072
*面對潮水 開始游泳*
*To face the tide and swim*

431
00:32:19,771 --> 00:32:23,810
*我游啊游啊*
*I swim, oh, swim*

432
00:32:24,075 --> 00:32:28,319
接著最後看起來奇怪的事 變得司空見慣
And, eventually, what seems strange becomes common.

433
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:32,587
看起來不可能的事 變得無比真實
What seemed impossible becomes real.

434
00:32:32,650 --> 00:32:37,895
*水已經沒過膝蓋 我該再等等 還是跳入水中?*
*Up to my knees now, do I wait? Do I dive?*

435
00:32:38,556 --> 00:32:40,485
*大海似乎很瞭解我*
*The sea has seen my like before*

436
00:32:40,485 --> 00:32:43,529
*雖然這是我第一次也是最後一次游泳*
*though it's my first and perhaps last time*

437
00:32:44,462 --> 00:32:49,844
*請叫我施洗者 請稱這是一場洗禮*
*Let's call me a Baptist, call this the drowning of the past*

438
00:32:50,268 --> 00:32:55,479
*她站在海邊 衝我背後扔石頭*
*She's there on the shoreline Throwing stones at my back*

439
00:32:55,540 --> 00:32:58,953
*所以游泳吧 直到你見不到陸地*
*So swim until you can't see land*

440
00:32:59,010 --> 00:33:01,820
*游吧 直到你見不到陸地*
*Swim until you can"t see land*

441
00:33:01,879 --> 00:33:04,985
*游吧 直到你見不到陸地*
*Swim until you can"t see land*

442
00:33:05,049 --> 00:33:08,792
*你是個人還是個沙包?*
*Are you a man or are you a bag of sand?*

443
00:33:11,389 --> 00:33:15,337
直到一切變得像以前一樣
Until things almost start to feel the way they used to.

444
00:33:18,696 --> 00:33:19,902
修好了 親愛的 跟新的似的
Fixed it, love. Working like a charm.

445
00:33:19,964 --> 00:33:22,171
好像一切都重新開始了
It's like it's all brand new.

446
00:33:30,675 --> 00:33:34,213
沃特 沃特 醒醒 醒醒      怎麼了?
Walter. Walter, wake up. Wake up.        Mmm. What?

447
00:33:34,412 --> 00:33:36,062
是亨利 他溜出房間 
It's Henry. He snuck out of his room. 

448
00:33:36,062 --> 00:33:38,020
又跑到車庫去了
He's down in the garage again by himself.

449
00:33:38,082 --> 00:33:40,323
好吧 告訴他回去睡覺
Well, tell him to come to bed.

450
00:33:40,385 --> 00:33:42,038
我知道 我每晚都這麼和他說 
I know. I tell him every night, 

451
00:33:42,038 --> 00:33:45,233
但是他得親耳聽到你說
but he needs to hear it from, you know, you.

452
00:33:46,190 --> 00:33:47,191
好吧
Yeah.

453
00:33:49,260 --> 00:33:50,603
我就來
I'm on it.

454
00:33:54,399 --> 00:33:57,608
喲 這麼晚了你要去哪?
Whoa, where are you going this time of night?

455
00:33:57,668 --> 00:33:59,875
我要去告訴那小傢伙讓他停手 我要睡覺
I'm gonna tell the little guy to knock it off so I can sleep.

456
00:33:59,937 --> 00:34:00,938
好吧
Right.

457
00:34:01,039 --> 00:34:04,418
我也要去那 來吧 我們去包抄他
I was going to the same place. Come on. Let's triple-team him.

458
00:34:05,376 --> 00:34:08,550
算了吧 你和你的毛茸茸朋友去吧
That's okay. You've got your little furry friend.

459
00:34:11,682 --> 00:34:12,683
晚安
Good night.

460
00:34:22,060 --> 00:34:23,869
除了球拍 你還在做什麼?
What are you making besides a racket?

461
00:34:23,928 --> 00:34:25,625
你也睡不著嗎?
You couldn't sleep, either?

462
00:34:25,830 --> 00:34:29,073
哦 夥計 事實上 我正睡得香
Well, actually, mate, I was having a brilliant kip

463
00:34:29,133 --> 00:34:31,340
接著就被你的崩崩聲給吵醒了
till you started banging away.

464
00:34:32,170 --> 00:34:34,047
我有個主意
I just had this idea.

465
00:34:34,105 --> 00:34:36,821
哦 什麼? 讓我們明天再想吧
Oh, yeah? Well, let's have the idea in the morning.

466
00:34:37,175 --> 00:34:39,712
就十分鐘 求你了
Just 10 more minutes, please?

467
00:34:39,777 --> 00:34:41,415
十分鐘 好吧
Ten more minutes, all right, yes.

468
00:34:41,479 --> 00:34:44,893
不過以後沒我在身邊不要亂動這些工具
But no more mucking about with tools when I'm not around.

469
00:34:44,893 --> 00:34:45,929
這很危險
It's not safe.

470
00:34:46,084 --> 00:34:48,758
媽媽和你說不要動 你要聽她的話 還有晚上也是
Or when your mother's asked you not to. Or at night.

471
00:34:48,820 --> 00:34:52,918
在廁所 在爬埃弗勒斯峰的時候
Or in a toilet. Or when you're climbing Mount Everest.

472
00:34:53,191 --> 00:34:54,761
還有捏鼻子的時候 同意嗎?
Or picking your nose. Agreed?

473
00:34:55,359 --> 00:34:57,236
同意      那你說吧
Agreed.        There you go.

474
00:34:59,964 --> 00:35:03,138
你能和我說話嗎? 我喜歡聽你說話
Can you talk to me? I like it when you talk.

475
00:35:04,068 --> 00:35:05,638
你想讓我說什麼?
What do you want me to talk about?

476
00:35:05,703 --> 00:35:07,182
隨便 隨便說說
Doesn't matter. Just talk.

477
00:35:08,739 --> 00:35:10,650
你的聲音很好玩
You have a funny voice.

478
00:35:11,642 --> 00:35:13,952
你很容易滿足 不是嗎?
You're quite easily entertained, aren't you?

479
00:35:17,582 --> 00:35:22,088
給你一個小電鋸 一塊木頭 再來一點嘮叨
Give you a buzz saw, a block of wood, and some chatter...

480
00:35:31,095 --> 00:35:33,024
嘿 沃特 你和他說了嗎?
Hey, Walter, did you talk to him?

481
00:35:33,030 --> 00:35:35,911
是啊 一切正常 他會回去睡覺
Yes, and everything's fine. He'll stick to the schedule.

482
00:35:36,167 --> 00:35:37,305
出什麼事了?
What's going on?

483
00:35:37,435 --> 00:35:41,076
我有了新點子 親愛的 現在得立刻投入工作
I've had a breakthrough, love. Got to get to work right away.

484
00:35:41,172 --> 00:35:42,173
現在?
Now?

485
00:35:42,240 --> 00:35:43,810
一刻都不能停
Not a moment to spare!

486
00:35:47,111 --> 00:35:48,818
你簡直是個女神
You're a goddess.

487
00:36:01,058 --> 00:36:03,504
先生 你今天真早啊
Sir? You're in early.

488
00:36:03,561 --> 00:36:05,871
說曹操 曹操到
Just the woman I wanted to see.

489
00:36:06,931 --> 00:36:07,932
看看這個
Have a look at this.

490
00:36:09,033 --> 00:36:11,843
現在 我們得馬上開工
Now, we need to get started on this right away.

491
00:36:12,370 --> 00:36:13,815
是一個海貍?
It's a beaver?

492
00:36:14,872 --> 00:36:15,907
這是未來
It's the future.

493
00:36:16,374 --> 00:36:17,375
就這個?
This?

494
00:36:17,642 --> 00:36:19,815
會說話的木質海貍
